import numpy as np
def plot_tree(model):
    n_features = X.shape[1]
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (16, 9)
    plt.barh(range(n_features), model.feature_importances_, align='center')
    plt.yticks(np.arange(n_features), cols)
    plt.xlabel(' ')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.ylim(-1, n_features)
plot_tree(forest)
